<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4153 To Avert From Men God's Wrath (Eb major)
Key: Eb (3 flats: Bb, Eb, Ab). Hymn has strong vi (Cm) and ii (Fm) color.

Non-diatonic subs: C major → Cm (vi); G#°/D° → Fm (ii) or Bb (V);
Dø7 → V=Bb for smooth dominant function.

mm.1-4: I "334" open, vi/I oscillation, ii7→V→I full sequence
mm.5-8: Building texture — I/V/vi/ii7/V patterns, 4-note LH throughout
mm.9-12: Final phrase mirrors opening, diverges at m.11 (ii passing),
  cadence ii→V→I with pedal Eb1 grounding.

VOICE LEADING: Ab4 in Fm/vi appears as tension note resolving to G4 (I).
  Bb F chain (bass steps 5th) provides strong cadential motion.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm.1-4: Moderate, 2-note RH, 4-note LH
mm.5-8: High register, 3-note RH climbing to D5, full sweep
mm.9-12: Settling, contrary motion, sustained final I
-->
